From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: IoT Gateway <dev@igw.local>
Date: Wed, 12 Nov 2025 20:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] init: print IGW hello line at late init

Add a minimal late_initcall that prints a single informative line
to the kernel log so we can verify kernel patching via Yocto.

Signed-off-by: IoT Gateway <dev@igw.local>
---
 init/main.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/init/main.c b/init/main.c
index 1111111111..2222222222 100644
--- a/init/main.c
+++ b/init/main.c
@@ -100,6 +100,15 @@
 #include <linux/init_syscalls.h>
 #include <linux/stackprotector.h>
 
+/*
+ * IGW learning patch: print a friendly line once during late init.
+ */
+static int igw_hello_init(void)
+{
+    pr_info("IGW: hello from kernel patch (late_initcall)\n");
+    return 0;
+}
+late_initcall(igw_hello_init);
 
 /*
  * Debug helper: via the boot commandline "debug_boot_weak_hash"
  * use a faster hashing function when calculating the boot cache hashes.
-- 
2.45.0

